  "title": "Shrinking 'Have' and 'Has'",
  "learningGoal": "The learner will master phonological contractions of Present Perfect auxiliaries against subjective pronouns (I've /aɪv/, You've /juːv/, He's /hiːz/, She's /ʃiːz/, They've /ðeɪv/, We've /wiːv/), increasing fluency and native conversational speed.",
  "difficultyLevel": "intermediate",
  "baseLanguage": "hi",
  "targetLanguage": "en",
  "estimatedTime": 45,
  "prerequisites": ["en_hi_M3B2_lesson_001"],
  "instructions": "In English, we rarely say 'I have eaten'. We squish the words together to speak faster: 'I've eaten'. This lesson will train you to make those native contraction sounds! Listen and copy the audio.",
  "contentItems": [
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "WARNING: 'He's' can mean 'He is' OR 'He has'. If an action word (V3) comes right after it, it means 'He has'! Example: He's gone = He has gone."
    }
  ],
  "targetPhrasesOrWords": [
